Q69:
I believe a nomenclature framework would be very helpful. Classification based on things like movement direction, position, and implement (amongst others) would help to define an easier way to communicate and search for exercises. For example: "dumbbell goblet reverse lunge" include the implement (dumbbell), position (goblet), and direction/movement (reverse lunge).

Of course there are exercises that have become popularized by a certain name that professionals just need to know, i.e. "Thruster", "Copenhagen", "Nordic hamstring". As digital exercise prescription tools become ubiquitous, such as programs like VALD's TeleHab, it is important that exercises be named in an organized way so that clinicians can search using known parameters.
